\nwith the highest-column-density cores being detected by SCUBA-2. For roughly\nspherical geometries, column density corresponds to volume density, and so\nSCUBA-2 selects the densest cores from a population at a given temperature.\nThis selection effect, which we quantify as a function of distance, makes\nSCUBA-2 ideal for identifying those cores in Herschel catalogues that are\nclosest to forming stars. Our results can now be used by anyone wishing to use\nthe SCUBA-2 GBS data set.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Aug 2016 18:26:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-24"}
